Overview of adj volatile

The adj volatile has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (2) volatile -- (evaporating readily at normal temperatures and pressures; "volatile oils"; "volatile solvents")
2. explosive, volatile -- (liable to lead to sudden change or violence; "an explosive issue"; "a volatile situation with troops and rioters eager for a confrontation")
3. fickle, volatile -- (marked by erratic changeableness in affections or attachments; "fickle friends"; "a flirt's volatile affections")
